Operating System

Operating Systems are the programs which sits at between a user and a Hardware. Operating system manages the hardware and helps in executing all the process in the hardware. 

What is Shell?

Shell is the program which helps communicate the user with the hardware, and acts as an interface. Types of Shells are:
-sh
-bash
-ksh
-ssh
-powershell

Shell act as intermediary between the user and the hardware to translate the commands provided and execute it on the hardware.

Is Shell a part of an operating system? Yes

Operating System has two main parts: Shell and the other is Kernel.

Kernel is the core compnnet of the Operating System that manages system resources and provides services to the other programs running in the system. It is responsible for 
the tasks like memory mangement, process scheduling and device drivers.

You cam use cmd.exe or Powershell as a command line shell to write script in Windows. For Linux, you can start with default Bash.

What are Mobaxterm and PuTTy used?
Mobaxterm and PuTTy are used for ssh clients to access remotely.
